{
  "texts": [
    "Participants submit complete source code, configuration, and model details along with their results, enabling the benchmark owners to directly reproduce outcomes.",
    "This is maximum reproducibility, but conflicts with potential IP concerns.",
    "Akin to Kaggle, users run models locally on the benchmark dataset, then submit only the predictions which are scored against hidden labels.",
    "This addresses IP concerns, but cannot know how predictions were generated.",
    "Users submit an executable model (e.g., via a Docker container) and the benchmark owners run the model against a hidden test set."
  ]
}